A mostly great app, but has some issues that need to be fixed. - The app has a prompt to log you in when you first launch the game, but will log you out. This is a problem because there is no way to log back in manually so it is impossible to gain score in the Challenge mode. - It's tedious to see how you rank in Challenge mode because of how they designed the standings. - There are also some bugs, like cards showing up facedown in the tableau so you don't know what you are getting.
totally adorable with a lot of strategy and methods to win

Several bugs that mar an otherwise excellent game. 1) catnip counts twice, once in the cat points and once as catnip points, making it overpowered (if you have 4 catnip and 8 cats, that's 32 points!). This is true at every player count & mode and is against the original rules. It makes catnip very OP. 2) You can't trade in cat posters on the turn you get them, adding randomness.  3) You can't move spray bottle after choosing cards. The last 2 can be fixed by adding a context-specific end-turn phase that happens only if person has 2 posters or a spray bottle. The first issue, however, is downright game-breaking.
replyContent: Hi Mariya, thank you for your review.  The catnip bug has been fixed in version 0.0.79 (released last week) and the spray bottle rules have also been tweaked to work closer to the physical game.

replyContent: Hey Nicole, great to hear you are pleased with the app. Online play is on our roadmap. Facebook is used to give us a "safe" username and picture to display on the leaderboards. There was a leaderboard for comparing with friends, but Facebook disabled that. Your last suggestion is great, we will display your points on the leaderboard.

content: Simple but fun game and the, sound effects are brilliant.

Excellent implementation of an equally excellent card game. The sound effects and music really add to the charm of the game and make it a joy to play. If you enjoy this brilliantly simple card drafting game, I highly recommend you consider picking up the tabletop version. There are a few errors with some of the stray cat cards: Moonbeam - Moonbeam's ability states "Moonbeam grants 2 wild food". This is incorrect and varies from the tabletop's ability, which states "You may use any 2 food as wilds". The original, and correct, ability allows you to use any 2 existing food as wilds, whereas the app's ability incorrectly gives you 2 wild food for free. Penny - in the app, Penny is a black cat. She should be an orange cat. This error will affect the balance of the game. Truffle - the first sentence of Truffle's ability states "feed Truffle 1 chicken, tuna, milk". This suggests you must feed her one of each food type. This is wrong. The correct text should read "feed Truffle 1 chicken, tuna, or milk". She must be fed only one item of any one type of food.
replyContent:
Thanks for the great comments, we're thrilled you're enjoying Cat Lady!
With Moonbeam's ability, to keep Cat Lady flowing as smoothly as possible we opted to have Moonbeam grant 2 wild food rather than requiring the player to manage which food they want to use at any given time.
We'll get right onto fixing your other two points though, thanks
